FBIS3-26206 "drchi024_k_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-024 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Feb 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Jiang Zemin Makes `Secret' Visit to Shenzhen HK0402065594 Hong Kong SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST in English 4 Feb 94 p 10 HK0402065594 Hong Kong SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST Language: English Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report] [Text] President Jiang Zemin made a secret trip to Shenzhen around January 23, according to sources in the Special Economic Zone. It is believed the party chief gave a generally positive assessment of the city in its role as a "national testing ground" for market reforms. And premier Li Peng, who was in Zhuhai this week, will reportedly make an inspection tour of Shenzhen before officiating at the opening ceremony of the Daya Bay nuclear power plant on Sunday. Shenzhen sources said Mr Jiang endorsed economic experiments in Shenzhen while asking cadres to keep down inflation and stay away from "unsubstantial investment plans".
